I'm declaring shenanigans on this constructor. We need a builder.
There's no reason in Java 8+ I should ever have to see the word null, let alone 9 in a row. But that may be another ticket.
If you don't want a builder, then your shorter constructors need to call the longer ones with default methods.
User createUser(A a) {
  return createUser(a, defaultB);
}

User createUser(A a, B b) {
  return createUser(a, b, defaultC);
}
// etc 

But a builder is still much preferred.

